review_blob: Really enjoy the Amarillo hops in this one, they balance the centennial to create a really nice aroma and flavor. Plus at only 5.5% you can have a few.
Ill always have a place in my heart for Sam Adams. All around solid lager with decent maltiness and a clean finish. If you cant respect a Boston Lager then I dont know if we can be friends.
This beer is super complex, so many different things going on, nice yeast character, crazy malt structure, sweetness, you name it. I love this beer, hope they re-release the special edition too.
Really nice orange color on this and massive hop aroma. Overall a pretty well balanced, yet hoppy, delicious pale.

This beer was wild, my buddy picked it up in London when he was visiting. Like most Fantome beers, you just a lot of funky yeast character, but has a curve ball of some coffee nice, worth trying for sure.
Always a classic, this beer has a great color for an IPA, and I love that there is a good malt character to it as opposed to only being hoppy
Damn good porter, this has a great roasted maltiness and very nice mouthfeel. Just enough sweetness is left behind to balance the roast.
Solid IPA, nice that you can always get it, and the price point is great. Some maltiness, and very good citrusy nose.
a classic, love that you can always get this, nice dank hops without being too much
Solid red ale, has a nice malt structure and when you can get it fresh, the hops come through nicely.
Really solid stout, love the notes of vanilla throughout, nice body, and good dark color.
great easy drinking pale, you can have a bunch of these and still function, and the aroma is awesome
beer_name: New Glarus Moon Man No Coast Pale Ale

review_blob: Love this lager, pretty much has become my goto, and it goes well with plenty of different foods.
